Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.31,0:00:11.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Shiiwaku, manabi... Huh? Fu-re? Re-re?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.40,0:00:14.95,Main,,0,0,0,,What was this one again?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.95,0:00:16.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Hang on a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.82,0:00:21.25,Main,,0,0,0,,"Characters you don't have to use the kun\Nreading for even if grammatically necessary."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.25,0:00:23.50,Main,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.50,0:00:25.54,Main,,0,0,0,,You're not supposed to read them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.71,0:00:33.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks for helping while you're\Nstudying for your test.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.59,0:00:35.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.01,0:00:38.89,Main,,0,0,0,,You gotta refresh yourself sometimes.\NMy mind was going blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.89,0:00:40.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Look how hard you're working!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.31,0:00:48.36,Main,,0,0,0,,I did really bad on my midterms,\Nso I at least want to work hard for the finals.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.36,0:00:51.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Really? That's a good attitude to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.19,0:00:54.45,Main,,0,0,0,,If there's anything you don't understand,\Nfeel free to ask Shun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.45,0:00:56.20,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he can teach you a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.20,0:00:59.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Wh-Why are you bringing up Shun?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.20,0:01:03.37,Main,,0,0,0,,He's so busy, I doubt he'd\Nhave time to help me anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.37,0:01:04.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.91,0:01:08.96,Main,,0,0,0,,It seems like you two and Waka have all\Nbeen studying together a lot lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.96,0:01:11.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka's mother told me all about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:11.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.63,0:01:15.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Th-That was... Waka's idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.47,0:01:19.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun's being very considerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.39,0:01:21.60,Main,,0,0,0,,I really do love him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.60,0:01:24.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Y-You love him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.61,0:02:59.07,Main,,0,0,0,,"Episode 7\NMorse's Inspiration"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.07,0:03:03.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Ayuhara! Ichikawa! Imai!\N"Episode 7\NMorse's Inspiration"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.12,0:03:06.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Eighty percent!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.79,0:03:10.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Ichikawa, an 80 is nothing to yell about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.25,0:03:11.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Hayase!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.08,0:03:12.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.46,0:03:15.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Himuro!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.38,0:03:17.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Fujita!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.55,0:03:20.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Matsuyama!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.63,0:03:22.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Mizuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.47,0:03:26.76,Main,,0,0,0,,She received the only perfect score\Nin the class today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.85,0:03:31.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Minami!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.81,0:03:33.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Murakami!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.27,0:03:37.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm just not any good at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.82,0:03:42.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Welco--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.83,0:03:52.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I just came here as a customer today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.37,0:03:53.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:03:57.21,Main,,0,0,0,,On your favorites menu,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.21,0:04:01.38,Main,,0,0,0,,it said you have a special chiffon cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.38,0:04:03.51,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.51,0:04:07.85,Main,,0,0,0,,We sold out of the Jersey Milk\NChiffon Cake this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.85,0:04:10.56,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. What a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.56,0:04:13.85,Main,,0,0,0,,I was hoping to take one back for a client.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.85,0:04:15.56,Main,,0,0,0,,A client?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.56,0:04:17.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Why would you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.90,0:04:21.19,Main,,0,0,0,,The fund we manage for her\Ntook a slight loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.19,0:04:23.20,Main,,0,0,0,,I was hoping to take it as an apology.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.20,0:04:25.32,Main,,0,0,0,,You, directly, Mr. Mikage?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:30.49,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm grateful to have such a\Nbeautiful woman remember my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.45,0:04:34.58,Main,,0,0,0,,She's a sixty-year-old industrialist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.58,0:04:37.63,Main,,0,0,0,,She's famous for her gourmet palate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.63,0:04:39.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Consideration is more important when we fail
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.96,0:04:43.80,Main,,0,0,0,,than when business is going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:46.26,Main,,0,0,0,,A woman with a gourmet palate?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.26,0:04:51.89,Main,,0,0,0,,In that case, what about our six types\Nof pudding, made with organic vegetables?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.39,0:04:53.89,Main,,0,0,0,,They're very popular with women
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.89,0:04:58.98,Main,,0,0,0,,who are concerned about\Ningredients, flavor, and calories.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.98,0:05:00.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.57,0:05:02.99,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll take that pudding, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.99,0:05:05.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.91,0:05:11.45,Main,,0,0,0,,You don't have to get so upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.49,0:05:15.33,Main,,0,0,0,,It's just the usual, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.33,0:05:20.21,Main,,0,0,0,,But I really studied hard this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.21,0:05:22.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari. What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.21,0:05:24.88,Main,,0,0,0,,She got her usual\Nawful score on our last test.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.88,0:05:27.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka! You don't have to put it that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.97,0:05:30.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.52,0:05:36.06,Main,,0,0,0,,B-Brother, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.90,0:05:41.65,Main,,0,0,0,,I found Dr. Hayase's thesis,\Nso I was reading it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.82,0:05:47.61,Main,,0,0,0,,"Regularity in Dimensional Distortions\NCaused by Changes in Electromagnetic Fields"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.61,0:05:52.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I think this is the basis\Nfor the machine he created.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.37,0:05:55.91,Main,,0,0,0,,It's written in Japanese,\Nbut I can barely understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.41,0:06:02.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah... the vocabulary is too\Nspecialized for me to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.21,0:06:05.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun is so amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.63,0:06:08.47,Main,,0,0,0,,He can understand it just by looking at it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.47,0:06:11.05,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't actually understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:13.10,Main,,0,0,0,,That's why I was looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:17.35,Main,,0,0,0,,If you keep looking at things you\Ndon't understand, and keep thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.35,0:06:19.94,Main,,0,0,0,,some day, it might all come together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.94,0:06:22.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.15,0:06:26.07,Main,,0,0,0,,So? What's with the strings\Nof letters and numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.07,0:06:29.20,Main,,0,0,0,,I believe this is the record of the\Narmillary compass's destinations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.20,0:06:34.08,Main,,0,0,0,,I think AM1 may be the doctor,\Nand AM2 could be Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.08,0:06:37.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Then we know\Nthe last place Papa went to?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.62,0:06:38.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.66,0:06:44.34,Main,,0,0,0,,If I could grasp the system behind\Nthese numbers and letters...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.34,0:06:46.84,Main,,0,0,0,,That's something you don't\Nunderstand yet, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.84,0:06:48.22,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:49.80,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.80,0:06:53.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't get so depressed.\NWe'll figure it out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.60,0:06:55.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Right, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.26,0:06:57.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.47,0:07:00.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, then... let's get started!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.48,0:07:06.82,Main,,0,0,0,,For now, I believe if you touch\Nany picture that's Morse or later,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.82,0:07:09.19,Main,,0,0,0,,you'll travel to the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.19,0:07:10.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.54,0:07:20.37,Main,,0,0,0,,“The Year 1825\N(What is Now) New Haven, America”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.59,0:07:33.01,Main,,0,0,0,,So cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.60,0:07:37.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.51,0:07:40.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh... um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.64,0:07:44.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, are you the scientist, Mr. Morse?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.02,0:07:47.90,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm not a scientist, but my name is Morse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.90,0:07:49.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:53.28,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm Mari. Mari Hayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.28,0:07:55.53,Main,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.53,0:07:57.53,Main,,0,0,0,,You just came from a burst of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.53,0:07:59.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.62,0:08:03.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Why are you crying, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.29,0:08:07.25,Main,,0,0,0,,My wife died last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.25,0:08:09.67,Main,,0,0,0,,When it happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.67,0:08:13.30,Main,,0,0,0,,I was off painting a portrait\Nof Marquis de Lafayette...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.30,0:08:17.35,Main,,0,0,0,,A portrait? Mr. Morse, are you a painter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.35,0:08:18.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.14,0:08:20.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.97,0:08:25.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, until he invented Morse Code,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.27,0:08:28.90,Main,,0,0,0,,it seems he was a skilled painter\Nwho gave lectures at universities.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.78,0:08:32.28,Main,,0,0,0,,But in 1825,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.28,0:08:35.41,Main,,0,0,0,,his wife died, and the news didn't\Nreach him at his place of work in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.41,0:08:38.70,Main,,0,0,0,,so he missed her funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.70,0:08:40.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.37,0:08:45.96,Main,,0,0,0,,This place on the monitor...\Nis it not synced with the book?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.96,0:08:48.59,Main,,0,0,0,,And these numbers here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.63,0:08:54.05,Main,,0,0,0,,It really looks like the\Nhistory of AM1, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.05,0:08:56.30,Main,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.30,0:08:59.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Just who are you talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.05,0:09:01.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.06,0:09:03.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, there's something I want to test.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.77,0:09:05.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.48,0:09:10.77,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm going to rewrite the coordinates of your\Narmillary compass to match the doctor's.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.77,0:09:13.24,Main,,0,0,0,,What will happen then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.24,0:09:17.28,Main,,0,0,0,,I think it will take you to\Nwhen the doctor met Mr. Morse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.28,0:09:19.91,Main,,0,0,0,,I understand. Try it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.91,0:09:22.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Matching up coordinates with AM2.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.91,0:09:25.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Battery remaining. Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.50,0:09:26.92,Main,,0,0,0,,How's Mari doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.92,0:09:28.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.96,0:09:31.30,Main,,0,0,0,,She's fine. No change!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.30,0:09:33.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Good. I don't think I'm missing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.51,0:09:34.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.92,0:09:36.47,Main,,0,0,0,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.72,0:09:43.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Morse! You're going to make\Nan invention that will change humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.97,0:09:47.19,Main,,0,0,0,,So don't be sad forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.56,0:09:52.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Sh-She disappeared?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.90,0:09:55.94,Main,,0,0,0,,What happened just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.65,0:09:59.70,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1832, on the Atlantic Ocean"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.30,0:10:17.42,Main,,0,0,0,,That hurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.42,0:10:20.43,Main,,0,0,0,,--Aren't you... that girl?\N--Mr. Morse!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.89,0:10:25.93,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought you were an angel or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.93,0:10:28.69,Main,,0,0,0,,I started thinking about\Na lot of things after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.69,0:10:31.61,Main,,0,0,0,,But I'm just an humble painter, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.61,0:10:35.44,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't think I could create an incredible\Ninvention like you talked about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.44,0:10:37.24,Main,,0,0,0,,People with no talent,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.24,0:10:42.12,Main,,0,0,0,,no matter how hard they work,\Nwill never accomplish anything great.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.12,0:10:43.66,Main,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:47.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm just not any good at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.33,0:10:51.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Luckily, I was blessed with artistic talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.33,0:10:54.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, I can live a decent life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.67,0:10:58.97,Main,,0,0,0,,It's amazing that you can make\Nsuch pretty pictures with only blip-blops...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.05,0:11:01.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Blip-blops?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.80,0:11:03.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, dots?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.72,0:11:06.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I am a professional, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.85,0:11:09.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes! I think that went well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.69,0:11:11.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.23,0:11:18.94,Main,,0,0,0,,It's from Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.94,0:11:20.45,Main,,0,0,0,,What could it say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.45,0:11:22.07,Main,,0,0,0,,What's going on with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.07,0:11:25.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother, you handle the rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.24,0:11:26.79,Main,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.21,0:11:31.67,Main,,0,0,0,,It's the ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.83,0:11:36.34,Main,,0,0,0,,This ship is going from Europe to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.34,0:11:38.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Then this is the Atlantic Ocean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.92,0:11:39.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.92,0:11:43.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, now, everyone! Your attention, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.80,0:11:46.76,Main,,0,0,0,,I have here a piece of copper wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.76,0:11:50.02,Main,,0,0,0,,And if I wind it around the iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.02,0:11:53.40,Main,,0,0,0,,then bring it close to the nails...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.40,0:11:55.61,Main,,0,0,0,,...nothing happens!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.61,0:11:56.94,Main,,0,0,0,,However!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.94,0:12:01.19,Main,,0,0,0,,If I bring the tip of the\Ncopper wire to this battery,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.19,0:12:04.03,Main,,0,0,0,,and run electricity through it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.03,0:12:05.70,Main,,0,0,0,,How mysterious!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.70,0:12:08.49,Main,,0,0,0,,All I did was wrap iron with copper wire!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.49,0:12:13.00,Main,,0,0,0,,And it becomes a magnet\Nthat attracts one nail after another!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.54,0:12:17.75,Main,,0,0,0,,And when I detach it from the battery...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.59,0:12:23.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow! Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.22,0:12:26.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh! Mari! You came at the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.39,0:12:27.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Help me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.64,0:12:32.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Help you out? W-With what?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.52,0:12:37.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Help you out? W-With what?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.19,0:12:39.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Never mind! Just step over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.36,0:12:41.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, now. The next trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.82,0:12:45.74,Main,,0,0,0,,When I re-attach it to the battery,\Nit's a magnet again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.74,0:12:48.12,Main,,0,0,0,,When it attaches, they stick!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.12,0:12:50.66,Main,,0,0,0,,When I take it off, they release!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.66,0:12:55.21,Main,,0,0,0,,This is the newest invention\Nof science, the electromagnet!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.21,0:12:57.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama! I want to do that, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.67,0:13:00.34,Main,,0,0,0,,You want to try? Step on up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.67,0:13:04.67,Main,,0,0,0,,It worked!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.67,0:13:06.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Amazing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.64,0:13:12.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, these electromagnetic kits\Nsell for just one dollar if you buy now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.47,0:13:15.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Perfect for a child's education!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.02,0:13:17.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Will it make them a doctor or a minister?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.69,0:13:18.86,Main,,0,0,0,,You're selling them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.86,0:13:21.44,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Mari?\NSell them! Sell them!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.44,0:13:23.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.19,0:13:24.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama, buy one!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.36,0:13:26.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your business!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.53,0:13:28.66,Main,,0,0,0,,No, we really can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.66,0:13:30.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Stop that. And give it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.58,0:13:33.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? No, ma'am! Don't be like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.91,0:13:36.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Everyone? W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.54,0:13:38.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Could I buy one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.58,0:13:39.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.71,0:13:41.17,Main,,0,0,0,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.38,0:13:44.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.97,0:13:47.22,Main,,0,0,0,,No matter how far away the line stretches,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.22,0:13:52.89,Main,,0,0,0,,it will attract or release\Nthe nails just the same, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.89,0:13:55.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.10,0:13:57.48,Main,,0,0,0,,An electromagnet, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.48,0:13:58.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Magnificent!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.48,0:14:04.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari. Thanks to you, I feel like I've been\Nable to see something I couldn't see before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.11,0:14:05.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.28,0:14:09.41,Main,,0,0,0,,If I can make a picture with dots,\NI'm sure I can make words with dots.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.53,0:14:14.16,Main,,0,0,0,,In that moment, Morse realized that\Nby turning an electromagnet on and off,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.16,0:14:16.20,Main,,0,0,0,,he could create words by\Ncombining dots and dashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.20,0:14:21.79,Main,,0,0,0,,In other words, long and short signals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.79,0:14:24.92,Main,,0,0,0,,This invention revolutionized\Nthe speed of communication,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.92,0:14:30.26,Main,,0,0,0,,which had previously been done\Nwith messenger pigeons and semaphores.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.26,0:14:36.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Electric signals opened the way to\Nlong-range communication for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.81,0:14:41.35,Main,,0,0,0,,He came upon the idea\Nseven years after his wife's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.35,0:14:45.07,Main,,0,0,0,,And twelve years after that,\Non May 24th, 1844,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.07,0:14:52.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Morse successfully sent the famous words,\N"What hath God wrought,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.66,0:14:57.50,Main,,0,0,0,,from Washington to Baltimore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.50,0:14:59.58,Main,,0,0,0,,That's your father, right, Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.58,0:15:00.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Erk!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.83,0:15:04.59,Main,,0,0,0,,W-Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.59,0:15:11.51,Main,,0,0,0,,I am an American doctor and scientist,\NCharles Thomas Jackson!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.51,0:15:13.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Ch-Charles?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.31,0:15:18.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.10,0:15:24.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you. You showed me an interesting\Ninvention, Mr. Charles Thomas Jackson.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.61,0:15:26.78,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad you believed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.78,0:15:27.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.40,0:15:30.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, yes... You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.24,0:15:31.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.58,0:15:42.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa... what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.00,0:15:43.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.83,0:15:46.04,Main,,0,0,0,,On the way back from Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.04,0:15:49.63,Main,,0,0,0,,he watched a demonstration\Nof the electromagnet on this ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.63,0:15:52.84,Main,,0,0,0,,and had the inspiration for Morse Code.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.84,0:15:54.22,Main,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.22,0:15:55.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.22,0:16:00.48,Main,,0,0,0,,The man who was supposed to\Ninspire him missed the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.48,0:16:04.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Does that make it okay for a\Ntime traveler like you to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.23,0:16:08.02,Main,,0,0,0,,And how do you know that, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.02,0:16:13.32,Main,,0,0,0,,W-Well... before the voyage,\Nhe had a bit too much to drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.03,0:16:17.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.12,0:16:19.08,Main,,0,0,0,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.08,0:16:23.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Well... he couldn't hold his liquor\Nthe way I expected...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.04,0:16:25.13,Main,,0,0,0,,You were drinking with him, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.13,0:16:30.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, I wasn't expecting him\Nto pass out drunk at two bottles!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.59,0:16:32.80,Main,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.01,0:16:37.64,Main,,0,0,0,,You're starting to sound like your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.64,0:16:39.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Because I'm her daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.52,0:16:45.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Even so, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.85,0:16:52.24,Main,,0,0,0,,The coordinates to Morse in that book\Nshould have been for 1825 in New Haven.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.24,0:16:55.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun rewrote the coordinates in the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.57,0:16:57.20,Main,,0,0,0,,That's Shun for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.20,0:16:59.78,Main,,0,0,0,,He's started to figure out\Nhow the machine works, has he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.78,0:17:01.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't try to change the subject!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.66,0:17:02.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Erk!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:06.21,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you even doing in the past, Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.21,0:17:08.50,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm discovering the secrets of that book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.50,0:17:09.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.42,0:17:11.96,Main,,0,0,0,,The book... You mean, you didn't make it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.96,0:17:13.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Certainly not!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.51,0:17:16.09,Main,,0,0,0,,I could never create anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.09,0:17:18.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.18,0:17:20.43,Main,,0,0,0,,I was just doing matter\Ntransportation experiments,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.43,0:17:23.22,Main,,0,0,0,,and that book suddenly transported to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.22,0:17:27.10,Main,,0,0,0,,It seemed likely that it\Ncame from the future. Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.40,0:17:33.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Oops, sorry. Looks like it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.28,0:17:35.28,Main,,0,0,0,,W-Wait! Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.28,0:17:40.62,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know what caused me\Nto go away for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.62,0:17:45.91,Main,,0,0,0,,But I think it's destiny that you\Ngot involved with that machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.96,0:17:52.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?! What's that supposed to mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.84,0:17:57.01,Main,,0,0,0,,What is it? Cut to the chase already!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.01,0:17:59.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Celebrate! We won the regional preliminaries!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.72,0:18:01.97,Main,,0,0,0,,The nationals are up next!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.97,0:18:05.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, I can study\Nand play soccer, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.18,0:18:06.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.85,0:18:10.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Our soccer club is in the nationals!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.86,0:18:12.90,Main,,0,0,0,,It's a miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.40,0:18:17.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. It is delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.20,0:18:21.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:26.29,Main,,0,0,0,,We've discovered Akira Hayase's background.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.29,0:18:30.88,Main,,0,0,0,,She's the eldest daughter of Renzaburo Miwa,\Npresident of the Miwa Concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.88,0:18:33.50,Main,,0,0,0,,When she was twenty, she moved to France,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.50,0:18:37.01,Main,,0,0,0,,and gained experience as a patissiere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.01,0:18:38.93,Main,,0,0,0,,The Miwa Concern...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.93,0:18:43.68,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. So she's unlikely\Nto be swayed by money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.68,0:18:48.35,Main,,0,0,0,,By the way, what about the book that appeared\Nduring the matter transporting experiments?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.35,0:18:52.90,Main,,0,0,0,,It seems to be a book about the\Nhistory of magnets and electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.90,0:18:55.86,Main,,0,0,0,,But that's all we know for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.86,0:18:57.49,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.03,0:19:05.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Would you like some, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.24,0:19:07.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.84,0:19:22.26,Main,,0,0,0,,She took them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.26,0:19:24.22,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.22,0:19:26.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun Mizuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.10,0:19:29.39,Main,,0,0,0,,In 2025, he developed the Law of\NTime-Space Abnormality Measurement
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.39,0:19:32.90,Main,,0,0,0,,that made time travel technology possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.90,0:19:36.82,Main,,0,0,0,,In 2076, he successfully\Ninvented the TSS limiter
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.82,0:19:39.65,Main,,0,0,0,,which prevented time paradox variations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.70,0:19:42.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.99,0:19:49.95,Main,,0,0,0,,W-Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.71,0:19:55.34,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.34,0:19:58.25,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm such an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.25,0:20:01.47,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't understand anything Papa's thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.59,0:20:04.68,Main,,0,0,0,,You're not stupid, Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.68,0:20:09.02,Main,,0,0,0,,But... even if I study,\Nmy grades don't improve.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.02,0:20:12.06,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't understand anything you guys do!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.90,0:20:19.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Everyone has lots of things\Nthey don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.15,0:20:21.36,Main,,0,0,0,,That's why you need to keep thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.36,0:20:24.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Stew over things. Investigate things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.16,0:20:26.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Even then, there are a lot of things\Nyou won't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.82,0:20:30.33,Main,,0,0,0,,But if you keep thinking,\Nthen one day, out of the blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.33,0:20:33.33,Main,,0,0,0,,everything will come together,\Nand you'll understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.33,0:20:37.29,Main,,0,0,0,,In physics, we call that\Nphase transformation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.29,0:20:39.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Phase transformation?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.80,0:20:41.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.09,0:20:45.55,Main,,0,0,0,,As water gets colder, there's an instant\Nwhen it becomes solid ice, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.55,0:20:46.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:50.43,Main,,0,0,0,,And at 100 degrees Celsius,\Nit becomes water vapor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.43,0:20:51.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.68,0:20:55.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Even things that, at a glance,\Nseem like they're not changing at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.35,0:20:58.56,Main,,0,0,0,,if you keep pouring energy\Ninto them, in one instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.56,0:21:01.57,Main,,0,0,0,,they'll suddenly undergo a physical change.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.57,0:21:05.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Study and inspiration are the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.45,0:21:09.24,Main,,0,0,0,,If you keep thinking,\Nyou'll undergo a sudden change?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.24,0:21:10.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.33,0:21:12.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Lots of people saw that exhibition,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.91,0:21:17.13,Main,,0,0,0,,but why did only Mr. Morse\Nhave the inspiration for the signal?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.13,0:21:18.38,Main,,0,0,0,,It must be because
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.38,0:21:24.05,Main,,0,0,0,,he had been thinking about the\Nlong-distance communication code for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.05,0:21:26.34,Main,,0,0,0,,There's no need to think\Nyou don't have any talent
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.34,0:21:29.39,Main,,0,0,0,,just because you don't\Nsee results right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.39,0:21:31.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.85,0:21:34.43,Main,,0,0,0,,What? What? What's with this vibe?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.43,0:21:36.02,Main,,0,0,0,,You'll be okay, Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.02,0:21:38.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Thanks, Shun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.94,0:21:42.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh-ho! Not bad at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.57,0:21:49.20,Main,,0,0,0,,"Learning without thought is labor lost;\Nthought without learning is perilous."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.78,0:21:53.54,Main,,0,0,0,,I see you're working hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.54,0:21:54.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.62,0:21:56.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Just because my grades don't go up right away
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.96,0:21:59.33,Main,,0,0,0,,is no reason to give up, I realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.33,0:22:02.50,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. That's very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.50,0:22:05.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Perseverance is important, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.42,0:22:06.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.47,0:22:10.39,Main,,0,0,0,,In physics, it's called phase transformation!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.39,0:22:12.18,Main,,0,0,0,,That's what Shun taught me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.18,0:22:15.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh? Shun said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.18,0:22:16.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.64,0:22:20.31,Main,,0,0,0,,That's my new almond praline cream puff.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.31,0:22:22.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Let me know what you think later.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.44,0:22:24.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.07,0:22:26.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay! Let's work hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.82,0:22:28.95,Main,,0,0,0,,"Next Episode: Bell's Decision"\NOkay! Let's work hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.95,0:22:30.11,Main,,0,0,0,,"Next Episode: Bell's Decision"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.20,0:24:00.79,Main,,0,0,0,,"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.79,0:24:03.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!\N"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.17,0:24:04.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.21,0:24:09.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Just what signal did Mr. Morse come up with\Nafter watching Papa's demonstration?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.84,0:24:13.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah! I really want to hear about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.13,0:24:17.10,Main,,0,0,0,,These are the transmitters\Nand receivers used in Morse Code.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.39,0:24:18.01,Main,,0,0,0,,"Transmitter"\N"Iron"\N"Electric Current" "Receiver"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.01,0:24:22.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Pressing the switch of the transmitter\Nsends electricity to the receiver,\N"Transmitter"\N"Iron"\N"Electric Current" "Receiver"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.35,0:24:25.56,Main,,0,0,0,,and turns the coil into an electromagnet,\Nwhich attracts the iron.\N"Transmitter"\N"Iron"\N"Electric Current" "Receiver"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.56,0:24:29.28,Main,,0,0,0,,When the electricity is cut off,\Nthe power of the spring pulls it away again.\N"Transmitter"\N"Iron"\N"Electric Current" "Receiver"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.28,0:24:33.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Morse thought of using\Nthis phenomenon to send signals.\N"Transmitter"\N"Iron"\N"Electric Current" "Receiver"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.24,0:24:35.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Morse is so smart!\N"Transmitter"\N"Iron"\N"Electric Current" "Receiver"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.70,0:24:35.91,Main,,0,0,0,,"Transmitter"\N"Iron"\N"Electric Current" "Receiver"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.91,0:24:36.70,Main,,0,0,0,,"Morse Code"\N"Short" "Long"\N"* This is modern Morse Code. It differs from the system devised by Morse."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.70,0:24:39.79,Main,,0,0,0,,And even more important\Nis that he figured out\N"Morse Code"\N"Short" "Long"\N"* This is modern Morse Code. It differs from the system devised by Morse."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.79,0:24:43.29,Main,,0,0,0,,a system of long and short signals\Nto express letters and numbers.\N"Morse Code"\N"Short" "Long"\N"* This is modern Morse Code. It differs from the system devised by Morse."
